<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-4026] CREATE2 requests embeded in a MULTI request only get a regular CREATE response</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-4026</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When making a MULTI request with a CREATE2 payload, the reply from the server only contains a regular CREATE response (the path but without the stat data).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See attachment for a capture and decode of the request/reply.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Connect to the ensemble&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make a MULTI (OpCode 14) request with a CREATE2 operation (OpCode 15)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Reply from server is success, znode is create, but the MULTI reply contains a CREATE (OpCode 1)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Tested with official docker hub images of the server and a python Zookeeper client (Kazoo, &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/python-zk/kazoo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://github.com/python-zk/kazoo&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
